{"text": "My only issue with this game is that, for whatever reason, after about 4-5 hours of playing, it will randomly crash. I don't know what was causing it, but as annoying as it was, it really didn't interfere with my experience that much. Revisiting this game in 2020, for me at least, is refreshing. I adored this game back in 2013, back when I was a kid and probably shouldn't have been playing it anyway, for its gameplay and its visuals. Coming back to it now much older was a significantly different experience. Not gonna lie, I totally got the idea to revisit it after watching Pyrocynical's in depth analysis of it, and I'm glad I did. It feels like a completely different experience playing a game about a 20 something year old piece of ♥♥♥♥ with irresponsible friends while also being a 20 something year old piece of ♥♥♥♥ with irresponsible friends; it feels more personal, and tailored toward me. It's because of that I feel both qualified to talk about that, and unqualified because of how biased I would be towards it lmao. In short, definitely play it. Pick it up if you've never tried it, or pick it up if you haven't played in a while because, in the words of IGN, \"It has a little something for everybody\".", "appid": "220240", "steamid": "profiles/76561198133713114", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599480000.0}
