{"text": "Based on what I've seen in my measly 10 hours in so far, this is one of the most realistic tactical sims that I have ran into. The best part for me is it depicts the cold war era, in fictional gone hot scenarios of course. I feel there certainly is no abundance of serious sims presenting this era, with WW2 heavily dominating the already niche genre. Simulation goes on in real time, but it can be paused at any time in normal mode or can be divided in \"turns\" of certain length of time. The passing of time, losses taken and timely control of tactical key areas defined at the start of each scenario are the factors deciding the outcome of the battle.  It's obvious a lot of effort has gone in to the background work, and the equipment typical for each time you pick a scenario/campaign for is meticulously modeled in. There are a ton of factors to take into account, and you really must have some kind of understanding of the equipment at your disposal and basic viable tactics to have success. Has somewhat of a learning curve, but not as bad as you might think at first look. Also there's a pretty good manual, and good gameplay videos in YouTube including the very basics of the game.", "appid": "1089840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198034907165", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1574769600.0}
