{"text": "Imagine playing the original Doom, in a single room, with endless enemies coming at you.  Throw in some leaderboards and instead of guns you are shooting daggers from your one hand.  What is the other hand doing?  No one knows. Now, set the difficulty at \"Hell on Earth\", and jump in.  Oh, wait, that should be \"Hell in Hell\", and, wait, again, there are no difficulty settings - it's just insane.  The abominations floating around the arena don't hesitate, they come straight for you, as if the devil daggers you absorbed at the start call to them like a beacon.  \"Come to us, destroy us!\" Can you last 500 seconds?  I've tried, and tried, and tried.  I can't hit 200 seconds.  It is fun, it is frustrating, it is intense.  Good luck in hell, you'll need it.", "appid": "422970", "steamid": "profiles/76561197987948166", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "33", "votes_funny": "7", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1511352000.0}
