{"text": "Henry Stickmin games, more specifically, Escaping the prison, was one of the first games I remember playing. This is a blast from the past for me! And a blast, it sure is!  Henry Stickmin collection is absolutely amazing. An amazingly hilarious story of one guy who wanted to break into a bank, and got far more than he could bargain for... Not only did he go to prison, he stole a diamond, he raided an airship, and he escaped a Russian prison camp. And now, with the final chapter, completing the mission, he must decide whose side to be on: The notorious Tophat clan of criminals? Or the U.S. army, whose plan is to end them once and for all? The choice is your's. This is an incredibly fun and well animated Choose your own adventure game. It's ridiculously over the top and crazy, featuring nonfunctional portal devices, giant robots, huge airships, move references, game references, and even a Jo-Jo's Bizarre Adventure reference. It's humor is incredible, it's insanely replayable, it's shockingly entertaining, and it's even got a good story. The last chapter in particular, Completing The Mission, has a fun story. You might just say, it was the best story yet... Overall, 8/10. A bit pricy, but absolutely wonderful for what you get.", "appid": "1089980", "steamid": "profiles/76561198110960935", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600776000.0}
{"text": "This mod and its community is pretty great. Joined a clan back in 2010 and nearly 9 years later that clan is now the community im leading. To fully experiance this mod in the best possible way here are some advices: 1. Community events. These are events such as linebattle, Pugs and siege and they are the best way to experiance this mod. They are usually hosted at specific times and there are steamgroups for them with further info and rules and such. 2. Talk to the people. Getting to know the community is important. 3. Join a clan. Joining a clan is a great idea if you enjoy playing the mod and maybe wanna become a bit better at it or you just want a greater challenge. Clan vs Clan battles can be anything from 5v5 smaller matches to huge linebattles. You also may end up in a clan where you feel like you dont fit in but you can always change clan until you find the group of people that makes your experiance better. I hope this helps // General Skill of 42Cdo", "appid": "1057700", "steamid": "profiles/76561197969948521", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "22", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1562068800.0}
