{"text": "yes I would recommend this game. HOWEVER: this game is lacking in depth. There is no tech tree. ship building is cool but very lacking. I feel like  my ship was built in the first hour and then I spent the next 15 hours in the first 5 systems. There were a few struggles for resources but after I over came those i had no trouble. and finally just rushed to the end cause I was getting bored.  I played about 21 hours which for me is not worth more then 5 bucks. there are other cheaper games with much more depth and I keep going back to them. This could be a great game that I keep coming back to but time will tell. The list of features planned will not be enough for me to even try to play it again.  What this game needs is a tech tree, engaging combat (ship/boarding), more interesting interaction with the members of your fleet, ability to change the heart of prisoners to join you (as it is right now i see no reason not to kill everyone and turn their bones into fertilizer), ability to make my people better at their jobs. more cosmetic ship options, a reason not to build a borg cube to make the most use of space for each ship, things to do (at some point I asked myself why was I still playing and it had only been 15 hours), diplomacy that matters (right now gaining reputation seems to be based on your current item/money stock so it is best to get rep up when you are poor and there is no compelling reason to get that rep up anyway).  Why I am recommending this game is because it wasn't bad so it seems to harsh to say no. I really wish there was a check back later recommendation because I want this game to get good and not die like so many other early access with this much potential. This could be the next FTL or Factorio or the next \"what was that game called? you know the reason i don't buy early access!\" I just looked over the features on the page and i must say the game as written seems cooler then the game i played. They do know how to spin lol.", "appid": "979110", "steamid": "profiles/76561198028238016", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1595505600.0}
