{"text": "For a free to play game in the zombie genre this game isn't bad at all. This game requires   yes,   whatsoever. To be fairly honest you can't even microtransact even if you desperately wanted to. The only part in this game where there is a payment option is to buy the   (Not considering certain community servers where they have their own microtransactions) But you don't really need to buy the soundtrack. As you can probably tell from other reviews, this game is pretty realistic and the graphics aren't that bad. Apart from the few graphical bugs that occur on occasion (for example when a prone zombie has half their body stuck in the wall), the rest of the graphics in the game comes out on top. I don't want to spoil any parts of the game for the people who haven't played it before but I can tell you that there are quite a few game modes with different \"storylines\" behind them. Overall, I'd give this game an 8/10 with my 30+ hours of gameplay and based on all the different content available. And anyway, it's a free to play game, so if you don't enjoy it, there'd be no harm done to your wallet.", "appid": "224260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198107465586", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "2", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1425643200.0}
