{"text": "My Review: Setting/Story - The third part of the series takes place in Brazil. Some players might see this as a poor decision to relocate the hero outside of New Jersey, but there was really no way to create a new story in the same setting. There are a few parts that take place in Panama and New Jersey in order to spice things up. The story could have been improved. The first Max Payne was well written. Wife and kid were killed by a junkie, kill all junkies and their suppliers. In the third part, Max Payne is hired to protect a rich family in Brazil that he does not really like... So there is a fundamental problem here. Who does Max Payne care for in this part? The blonde bimbo sister? The brunette bimbo sister? The spastic brother in law? The people of Brazil? We don't really know... 3/5 Shooting - Max Payne is known for the bullet time action. However, there have been a few changes in each part. In the first Max Payne you were limited to the \"Dive\" bullet time. The second one added more options for bullet time, and in the third they expanded even more. This is where the problems occur... The environment in this game is a lot more complex (due to the taking cover feature) and it stops you from using the dive bullet time efficiently. Not only that, but even the last chance bullet time is bugged due to objects that stop you from turning around and spraying down your target. The part that was really impressive was the cover feature. Shooting baddies from behind a desk with no aim like a baddie is something that I could do all day/night long. 3/5 Graphics - Really impressive for the most part. The environment is rich with details and this adds to the shooting experience. Intense gun battles make wood and glass chunks fly all over the place creating an intense environment without really reducing the visibility. However, all these cool things make the game file uncool. If you have slow internet and you have to download the game. CYA HICK. You will need a pretty decent PC to run this baby, but it is worth it. 5/5 Overall - Straightforward third person shooter that will provide you with a few days/weeks of entertainment. Don't expect an open end world with puzzles and freedom. This is a classic hallway cleaner. Enjoy", "appid": "204100", "steamid": "profiles/76561198044518234", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1390305600.0}
