{"text": "Don't let the Korean-style UI push you away from this game. What an absolute masterpiece. The sheer amount of things to do leaves you stuck in where to go next. More expensive items are surprisingly attainable. I got a horse within about 5 hours of playing, and I didn't spend any real money in-game, and I wasn't really focusing on my main questline. Buy this while it's on sale, for sure. The larger purchases include extra stuff that's actually worth what you're paying for it, and doesn't really put you at an advantage over other players, aside from the horse that you get. I only purchased the $5 version while on sale, and I got that out of the character creator alone. It's very in-depth. Make sure to mention traps or Alienware laptops in the server chat and watch the hilarity ensue. (For Alienware laptop users.) My keyboard lighting is controlled by the game, and I haven't put effort into changing it, but just a bit of a warning to those who are photosensitive. The pulse in the lighting will ramp right up, depending on what you're doing in-game. Your regular settings will return upon exiting the game. (For Discord users.) I had to start Discord in Admin mode to get push-to-talk to work with the overlay of Black Desert. There's no reason to be concerned about this, it's just a simple overlay incompatibility. Same with any other programs that may use PTT. Get some nice audio gear and indulge in this. I have some $10 Skullcandy earbuds and they work just fine.", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198043848988", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1517140800.0}
