{"text": "A rather fun if short metroidvania-ish platformer for a fair price (I actually got it on a 70% off sale).  It's pretty hard, so much of the ~5 hours it took for me to finish (with 100% completion) was spent dying and retrying from last savepoint.  And probably a half hour was spent looking for the final area containing the final boss.  The area before the final boss was actually pretty frustrating - a bit more and I might have put the game on indefinite hold. Thankfully after I managed through it there was a save point right before the final boss door, just as there was before all the other full bosses (though not mid-bosses.) A word of advice to future players - there's an optional item you can find that effectively gives you an extra life - but only once, and then it breaks.  Dying twice while having it sends you back to last savepoint and the item is effectively restored - after all it's reloading the save.  If you reach another savepoint after dying just once though, you'll never get the item back.  So if you die while wearing the item anywhere BEFORE that final area before the final boss, do yourself a favor and suicide (not IRL ofc). Another word of advice - after launching the game and seeing the image with the Xbox 360 Controller, don't mash buttons until the menu comes up - it'll come up on its own.  In fact it comes up behind that 360 controller image, so if you mash buttons you might accidentally start a new game, losing your progress, and nobody wants that.", "appid": "940830", "steamid": "profiles/76561197996495980", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1573560000.0}
