{"text": "Main game till level 95 out of a 100 can be reached in about 3-4 hours then the last 5 levels will all depend on HOW GOOD YOU ARE WITH MECHANICALLY PRECISE MOVEMENTS It appears to have Clustertruck(as stated by a reddit user) as an inspiration and that caught me since i haven't played a game like that. For a MAJORITY of the game you can freely swing from various surfaces with no timelimit but with a time counter to see how fast you can finish.  Its in the final 5 levels where people are having issues since the difficulty spike is so high. Each stage (personal 95-99) will take several retries but probably still less than an hour each stage. It requires fast reflexes and a time limit for some stages. I tried the last stage for 3-4 hours and made it until the halfway point before i just got bored Pros - Levels  1 till 95 are fun - Clustertruck feel  Cons - Difficulty spike for the final levels are too high(specially the ACTUAL level 100)", "appid": "811870", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084385268", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1596888000.0}
