{"text": "Estranged: Act II is a first-person adventure video game with stunning graphics. Combine adventure with certain hints of horror and puzzles, and all thanks to the exquisite work of developer Alan Edwardes. Without a doubt an interesting title that is worth trying.Surely you're going to win a good time of entertainment, because it's really good... Remember that Estranged: Act I followed the story of the weigher stranded on a mysterious island during a very violent storm. Now, the video game follows the adventure started in that opening title, when that heroic fisherman tries to return home, but he stumbles upon a secret corporation called Arque, and investigates further into his dangerous secrets. Highly recommended title if you liked the mystery in general, with a great atmosphere.", "appid": "582890", "steamid": "profiles/76561198003818180", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "7", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591531200.0}
{"text": "This summary is about everything I have to say about the game, really. Most of the core gameplay is hard grind. You gather resources and explore the world and gain LP -- points, which you unlock new items with.  There are PvP and PvE-servers. PvE are bland and are only good to learn the game. The main gameplay is on PvP servers: you gather stuff and raid your neighbors (be that online or an offline raid), which ultimately leads to reducing your grind. All in all, if grind's not for you, you will highly unlikely enjoy this game.", "appid": "829590", "steamid": "profiles/76561198005271335", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "19", "votes_funny": "3", "early_access": true, "tstamp_created": 1588161600.0}
