{"text": "the game is very fun, but there are some problems in the game that still feels, for me at least, that should be fixed or changed.  the game is a THIRD PERSON and FIRST PERSON SHOOTER, with the idea of the battle royale category, like PUBG and Fortnite, and like other battle royale games, the game plays as a big free for all deathmatch, that highlights the idea of big maps, weapons collecting, high number of people in one game, one respawn and death per match and a map that gets smaller while  the match runs. this idea of gamemode does plays good and fun, and the game got great graphics, but this game still lacks, not in terms of gameplay or graphics, but in term of game metirials, more spacific, maps rules and desine. here for me are the reasons why: - the game lets you choose before the match starts where to land, which i think is a bad idea for the players, because you can't know where yo should really land until you see other players players jumping from the plane (like in PUBG or Fortnite), and know where there will more likely be less to none players, and there to land. - the other thing is that the maps are to big. while it could be a good idea in this king  of games, but not in H1Z1. the maps filled with small cities and long lands with big mountians between them. that things makes you, as a player, run from city to city searching for weapons while bieng too expose to snpers and cars, instade of with maps with big cities, that makes you less expose, and combat will be more fair because of playing more against meduim to small range weapons like automatic rifles, then against long range guns like sniper rifles, a battle against far distence player, with more edventage then you. - the third and last thing is that, like the starting spawns, the safe zone shown in the match's map before the match even started, thing that makes most of the players spawn in the middle of the map, instade of other random places in the map. that thing destroys the fun, because it makes that if you start in the sides of the map you will be running with weapons from city to city, running to stay in the safe zone, playing against non-players, until somebody kills you from far away, bieng the 2th place in this match, even know you didn't killed a single player throw-out the match,  just run armed, bored, from one place to other, while treing to find players to fight against. but in the end, the game H1Z1 is a very fun game with good graphics, that really helped the battle royale idea to grow, and you should play it if you like battle royale. the game is also free to play on steam now, so if you regrate playing it, and even if you liked it, you still have nothing to loose. list of pros and cons: pros: - free game - good graphics - fun and addictive gameplay. -most of the gameplay content included inside the game (not pay to win game). cons: - choosing spawns pre-match. - small cities in the game map, with big open areas in between. - auto safe-zone shown pre-match. game settings: - battle royale game. - FPS/TPS. - big maps. - up to 100 players per match. - violent game. - strategy game. - reqiure skill and luck to win. - long games. - one spawn and death per match. - requir meduim computer conditions to run. i give this game 8.3/10", "appid": "433850", "steamid": "profiles/76561198166364533", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1513598400.0}
