{"text": "is a nice, rather short but still quite interesting, atmospheric sci-fi visual novel. Plus, it's free and has achievements, there's a steam guide if you have some trouble finding them all. So, I'd definitely recommend to have a look at this novel. There are just three characters in the story, including MC. But all of them are quite fascinating. MC's sprite is cute, by the way, as art in general. I wish there were a gallery for CGs, I know there're not many of them but it's still a convenient way to check how many you still miss, need to achieve, to reach them later without searching in the game. Among all characters, I especially liked to see a non-binary prisoner, an alien. Tho the appearance was a bit jarring to look at. Please, ppl, don't be offended but for my stereotypical self who lives in a conservative country and doesn't meet such ppl irl, aliens seem as the only variant I could imagine without any gender identification... Sex/gender may be not important, I can totally get it but you still belong to one of 2 types created by mother nature. It's still hard to grasp something non-existent but in this game, looking at the alien, for the first time I wasn't thinking about them in terms of he or she, the only possible way for my native language but, you know, they were a non-binary character indeed. That was an amazing, totally new experience. For that I am grateful.    Despite being a short story the game deserves the tag “Story Rich”, there's quite a number of endings. One good for each character and lots of bad endings. I absolutely enjoyed bad ones. I kinda appreciate well-written bad endings more than good ones. Happy endings in romantic stories are always kinda identical but suffering can be so versatile, so potentially emotional and impressive. Though some of bad endings I personally found hilarious, I literally was laughing. By the by, English is quite good, I liked the writing, though I came across a couple of typos, as usual.    So, a dramatical sci-fi novel about war and its repercussions, love and important life-changing decisions; partially voiced, with cute art, and absolutely free. Ideal for a couple of hours relaxing reading in the evening. Definitely give this one a try!", "appid": "1100270", "steamid": "profiles/76561198234584076", "voted_up": true, "votes_up": "15", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581854400.0}
