{"text": "I've always liked when games do the time loop thing where you repeat the cycle of a certain time period in order to achieve a better ending. For some reason, I did not like this game enough to finish the ending. Perhaps it was due to the massive difficulty spike when you encounter the final boss, or that I was starting to get tired of this gimmick. Either way, one thing's for sure, the way this game handles the story is not immersive as you act as a higher being that most does not seem to be entwined with the lives of the characters you \"bond\" with. Being able to go back in time multiple times until you find the right path also somewhat takes the sense of urgency away.", "appid": "455820", "steamid": "profiles/76561198009675436", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1581249600.0}
