{"text": "Killing NPCs is deliciously rewarding as headshots result in a wonderful therapeutic shower of blood and screams of agony of your enemies. Enjoy a rush of dopamine as you squint your eyes and take out well camouflaged enemies hiding in god-awful spots while firing infinite bullets from a 6-shooter.       However be prepared to rip your hair out, smash your keyboard to bits and hurl your mouse at the wall while you retry dueling a nemesis over 20 times, all while listening to that smug sound effect that comes after you've been shot and defeated over and over and over by an AI whom is obviously cheating. (This is the deal breaker, 0/10)  Basically, fighting your way to the boss is way more fun than actually fighting the boss.", "appid": "204450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198084700923", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1454846400.0}
