{"text": "This was the most boring visual novel I have ever played, hands down. I took a chance because I had tunnel vision on the reviews that mentioned Higurashi vibes, and after playing SubaHibi someone said, oh, that sounds a bit like CC. I have only played the steam edition so maybe the fan translation with H content was better but this was such a waste of time and money. Honestly. Do not even buy it. Go find some other version and try it. If you have to buy it go ahead but please notice the negative reviews. I don't know how this has a Very Positive rating, it is so hard to get through. I have so many hours because I really thought it would have some amazing twist that would make it redeemable but the one or two twists were NOT worth slogging through this boring, repetitive bull.", "appid": "812560", "steamid": "profiles/76561198049485115", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "10", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1594123200.0}
{"text": "I'm really on the fence on this one, even as a Arcade Racer fan primarily. I did enjoy Project Cars 1 and 2 whenever I felt like playing something in Simulation. Project Cars 3 isn't bad either, but having it named 'Project Cars' gives this game a vibe to where it's having a big identity crisis, it's one thing that isn't sitting right with me. Now the game, is it great? No, I'd honestly give it a \"Good\" rating, it's a mix of good and bad. It feels like an Arcade Racer, it is an Arcade Racer. I'm mostly sold on the VR aspect, it was a pleasant experience. Now, would I recommend this? Honestly, not at full price. The game looks and feels like $30 at best, I do a feel burned out as I did have more expectations, I'll still be playing this game regardless as it's still entertaining me. I'm not going to burn this game because \"muh pitstops and tire ware reee!\". Yes, it's an entirely different game, I feel like they should've gave the game a different name.  Even if you do wait, there's a chance more will be added and improved. I certainly wish it does happen, there's still potential. However, the amount this game still offers with a full $60, I gotta thumbs down after. TL;DR Sim Racer became Arcade Racer, stick to Project Cars 2 for Simulation Experience.", "appid": "958400", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078811539", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1598616000.0}
