{"text": "Not a bad game at all if you like Chess. Problem is, the game is severely lacking in content (maps and chess piece models). It barely comes with anything and the DLCS are overpriced, most of which suck from the looks of it. If more effort went into options, maps, and chess pieces for the game instead of DLC, it could have been much better and more varied. Even if the price was increased for the base game it would have been worth it. Also the DLC is overpriced at full price even if you do like a few of them. As for the A.I., not sure how good it is but I don't think it is terrible. However, I am sure there are other chess games with better A.I.", "appid": "518060", "steamid": "profiles/76561198061656944", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "13", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1591531200.0}
