{"text": "It's one of these games that were made for a student's project and released on Steam with hopes of easy money. Premise is simple - defend the guy lying on the ground. You move your bot around and shoot bots/deflect lasers. Left button is for shooting, right button is for slowing down time. If I'm not mistaken there are 4 types of attack patterns of your enemies - random bots spawning and driving towards the middle, random bullets shot from edge of the screen, one stream of bullets that circles around, and a single bot driving and shooting. Once your hero - or rather the guy that you're supposed to protect - is being hit 5 times, the game ends. There's no score, no wave counter or anything, so screenshots aren't showing what you're getting. I don't think you can \"finish\" the game, it's more about how long you can  survive, but you'll get bored in 5 minutes tops. It's only for card farmers once it's heavily discounted.", "appid": "568450", "steamid": "profiles/76561198025276799", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "3", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1565524800.0}
