{"text": "I don't even know how to start this. The idea behind the game is kinda innovative and interesting, but that's about it. Short review: Not worth your time or money, just skip this one. Long review: There are 3 bars that make barely any difference and your healt, the one that actually matters. You can attack only when standing which makes dodging impossible. Did I mention that attacking is an automatic mechanic that activates when your standing near an enemy? Yes, you don't need to attack, game does it for you. The levels are extremly linear. There is always only 1 correct way to go and turning to a side street is a dead end. There are also no poiters showing you where to go, which won't matter when you realise you just need to keep moving right. Enemy AI is as basic as it gets, always running at you from all sides. Enemy spawns are random and they spawn endlessly until you reach safe area, which means making a wrong turn forces you to battle 5-6 more \"breeds\". Many game mechanics don't work at all. Example: you do less damage when tired- I kill enemies in 2 hits both when tired and on full energy. Also I found a lot of crates that can't be opened, which is not explained at any point. I believe those to be weapon creates meaning you're stuck with your starter weapon. Animations in this game are quite bad, considering only you and enemies move, and it looks like both you and them have a stick up your butts. The music is generic, nothing more I can say about that. The voice acting was ok, alto there were only 3-4 lines on the game start. Graphics are generic too. I can't choose between unity assets or devs just not trying at all. All in all this is a game you should just skip.", "appid": "744440", "steamid": "profiles/76561198112347819", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "31", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1512475200.0}
