{"text": "It's not a bad fighter, for a Capcom game. A nice selection of characters Very nicely detailed, a little better than \"UMVC3\" Better detailed backgrounds/stages Way too pricey for a fighter Requires 60 gigs of hard drive space, unlike \"UMVC3\" which only needs about 5.6 gigs \"Deluxe Edition\" doesn't allow you all the DLC Not as many characters to choose from compaired to \"UMVC3\" Because it's from Capcom, it's your typical fighter. Choose your fighter and just fight away. They did a very good job with detail and making the characters seem more life like. The stages are also an improvement over the \"UMVC3\". I am not as amused about the loss of character selections. You would think that the idea if making a better \"Marvel Vs. Capcom\" fighter game would mean more fighters to choose from, but that is not the case. So far, only \"Marvel Vs. Capcom 2\" has their highest selection of characters, which is 56 fighters. I am super disappointed that I purchased the \"Deluxe Edition\" and still didn't get the additional DLC that they made afterwards. I paid a pretty hefty price for a deluxe game that will not include the additional DLC that they will make in the future. Seems as though Capcom's idea of \"Season Pass\" or \"Deluxe\" means \"You only get what we decide to give you and you will be thankful\". After seeing what they are doing to \"Street Fighter V\" as well as this game, I am thankful that I will be waiting to purchase other Capcom games from this point on. I used to be a huge fan of Capcom games for a long time, but after this mess, maybe now I need to be more careful about their games. This will be my last time I purchase any game from Capcom, either as early access or \"Deluxe\". Based on the evidense so far, this will probably mean that the next installment of this title will mean at $40, you start with 10 characters, and then you have to purchase the additional 40 characters/stages as DLC for $2.99 each & \"Season Pass\" will only give you 10 characters/stages. 1.) \"Deluxe\" usually implies that we get additional stuff for the game, my fault for assuming we get everything 2.) Additional skins don't improve the game because it doesn't give us additional characters 3.) Usually the next installment of the game is to add \"more\" content than the previous game 4.) What's with all the \"Resident Evil\"/\"DMC\" characters, there are TONS more Capcom characters 5.) How about additional characters from say... oh... I don't know... \"Darkstalkers\" or \"JoJo's Bizarre Adventure\" 6.) How about putting back some of the missing moves for some of the \"Marvel\" characters", "appid": "493840", "steamid": "profiles/76561198022104383", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "24", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1515499200.0}
