{"text": "First of all im a great fan of the Red Orchestra/ Rising storm Franchise, specially the first ones. Having said this i liked RS2 quite alot, the enviroment of the vietnam war, the classes, weapons and the mechanics were nice as well. The community prior to the release on Epic games store and its update was overwhelmingly friendly, consisting of a very large portion of Franchise veterans such as myself and new players that for the most part worked in team. The worst thing then was trying to find a server to join as most were always full by the time i came online and fps drops on Hue city map only(for me) but other than that the game ran smooth \"per se\". After the last update and the release of the free to play version on Epic Fail store i have played on several servers and saw: - Hackers( 1 dude was in mid war killing everyone, passed trough walls etc); -Lag in every server, even if you join your regular server with 40 ping you will get over 200 or 300 ping for no reason; -People teleporting all over the map and into the air( due to the 2 above stated reasons); -Epic game store owners cant join servers with players from Steam owners. At this point this game is unplayable to everyone, and bear in mind that altough i enjoy RS2 alot and the devs are prob working on a solution il give this game a negative review as in comparison to the previous title and  even RO1 and RO2 because RS2 is trashcan material at this point. I also recommend  all \"old\" veterans to return to RO2 and RS1, as the games are getting an influx of new players as well and even some new ppl coming from RS2.", "appid": "418460", "steamid": "profiles/76561198021772462", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "32", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1602417600.0}
