{"text": "Trying to find good chess game that is not against another human is pretty difficult to be honest. Steam doesn't have much of them, and those which are here are below-average. Chess Titans which is free to everybody who have Windows is way more advanced than this.  Me myself, I'm proud chess player. I love chess. I used to play chess as a kid. I used to go to some chess courses when I was in elementary school. But chess is not appreciated by majority. Not even by my mother LOL. She's saying it's useless but she's watching television garbage whole freaking day. Anyway, people who thinks that chess is game of nerds and geeks is literally and simply ♥♥♥♥♥♥. Take this L.  Chess Knight 2 is game no different than other chess games. It has nice visuals, but still Chess Titans looks way better. I believe there's no reason to say anything about mechanisms, chess is worldwide known game. But things, we should mention is AI, which is truly and really weak. Yes, it has 4 difficulty levels, but even on those it's easy. Simply, AI can't handle that.  Game offers multiplayer, local multiplayer and even playing on same screen, game have trading cards but it's just not enough to cover flaws. Not even achievements would help. Game was part of big bundle for 1 dollar, but it still doesn't mean it's worth that 1 dollar, so don't even think about 4,99.  Only positive thing about Chess Knight 2 was the actual fact it's about chess and that's it. And yes, I do appreciate that EnsenaSoft made actual chess game, but yeah, that's it folks.", "appid": "526880", "steamid": "profiles/76561198078193056", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "46", "votes_funny": "10", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1493985600.0}
