{"text": "This game is complete ♥♥♥♥. I am sorry that I wasted two hours of my time on it. Konami did everything to make the new part not pleasant to play. Terrible menu, annoying music and horribly scripted gameplay. Career mode is made AWFUL. Not only were Konami too lazy to make a generator for creating their own trainer, but they also made this generator almost identical in the players career as in the last part of the game. Instead of creating your own trainer character, you have to choose from existing legends such as Hendrik Johannes Cruyff, Diego Maradonna, Lothar Mateus and others. I am ashamed that my favorite footballer of all time, Johan Cruyff, is featured in this game! The menu of this game is just awful. I have no words. In the coach and player career mode, this menu looks crumpled and as cheap as possible. The gameplay initially gave me pleasure, but after playing a little longer I was very mistaken. Do you have a 90+ rated player? Be prepared for the fact that he will not be able to handle the ball. Is Messi small and technical? Hold my beer, it will be overtaken by every dummy in defense with a lower rating. I did not say anything about the lack of many licenses in PES 2020. Those licenses that they have are implemented quite well. As for the faces of the players: somewhere it looks better at PES, somewhere at FIFA. In this part, I especially liked how Konami made the kits. Looks very beautiful. Unfortunately, the PES wants to be too realistic, but they do not quite succeed. It is not interesting to do feints in PES, I do not get as much pleasure from this here as I would have in FIFE. I am not a supporter of FIFA, but this year PES specifically lost to them in competition.", "appid": "996470", "steamid": "profiles/76561198362970666", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "4", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1597406400.0}
