{"text": "This a nice puzzle games with interesting ideas, and it's not an easy game, some levels are quite challenging. Ultimately I sadly cannot recommend this game as the controls and the gameplay are quite bad:   - Each level begins with an animation that is long and unskippable. This is particulary annoying when you have to restart a level, as there is no way to restart without quitting the level and restarting and rewatching the level.   - The game is mostly keyboard driven: you move the blocks using the keyboard and switch blocks using keyboard or the mouse. It feels a bit awkward using the mouse just for that so it's more natural to use only the keyboard. However, the only way to navigate menus is with the mouse. Which means you use the mouse in the menus (to start a level or to quit a level: esc does not work) and the keyboard during the rest of the game, this is painful. Playing with a controller does not solve the problem as it only emulates the keyboard part   - Due to the way the camera is oriented, you don't see everything on the screen, due to blocks being hidden by other blocks. You can only rotate the camera 90 degrees, which doesn't always help. It becomes a problem later on and the developer actually acknowledges it on level 13 when the tutorial even says that sometimes you have to move your blocks just to see what happens !    I ultimately chose against recommendation due to all these technical issues that ruin the game for me. The first two are easily patchable and I might change my review if this changes.", "appid": "334300", "steamid": "profiles/76561198086659676", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1495886400.0}
