{"text": "This was my favorite and also one of the best true action MMO RPG games, dodging in real time, no bs standing there like a plank of wood, waiting to be hit by an attack and roll your face over the keyboard to start comboes like other MMOs. It's an old game, but it has large variety of classes, skill based gameplay, plenty of unique weapons, enemies, raids, costumes etc ! TL:DR - game is dead, heavily infested with payment ways, unforgiving gear enhancing system, community has been killed and the good people left Vindi long ago, it's poorly optimized and honestly sad to see it's state nowadays, so avoid it, you're no longer playing the good Vindictus, you're playing a former shell of a game which has nowhere to go, support is dead, community dead, just let the game peacefully die and please, read up on the dmg that Nexon as publisher has done, so that you avoid supporting them, they have killed many games, including this one. It's just a shame that it has been long dead, due to Nexon being absolutely the worst, they have destroyed the community around this game, with 0,02% drop chances of loot from raid bosses and you've needed that loot in order to craft a raid gear, which week or two later all parties required you to have, in order to even join the raid itself. Another nail in the coffin was weapon enhancing and enchanting, which on higher levels could and often WOULD BREAK YOUR WEAPON and GEAR. You HAD TO enhance and enchant your gear, in order to keep progressing through the game, to get stronger, to attack faster, to keep playing the relevant content. And your items literally broke in the pursuit of wanting to play more. Nexon has created a huge gap between people with RNG, some players would randomly get raid drops on one character, while others kept running the raid for 20, 40, 60 runs and would never get anything. All of the above has caused for the community to be split in half, on the normal players and elitists. And game has started to die ever since that has happen, people would quit due to their most valuable gear breaking,  gear that took hundreds of hours. People would quit disgusted with Nexon, how they kept lowering the hidden \"Luck\" value for events and start selling items which increased your Luck for real money, items which protected your gear from breaking, more and more leaning towards pay to win, but also Pay to be a lazy elitist, with no skill, no hard work behind your gear. It's sad that one of the best MMO RPG's has basically died, population of once thriving servers lowered to almost zero, all because of complete and utter GREED that Nexon has presented over the lifespan of this game.  Good night Vindictus, we've all enjoyed you for hundreds/thousands of hours, back when the game was playable only through the website, when we had just the starting classes in the game, when Scythe Evie was just for fun, because her dmg was super low. They used to have weekly events that would bring people back and we'd grind in this peaceful game, enjoy ourselves, relax and play together, game had a nice story for the first version and the community was helpful bunch, you'd revive each other with a feather, cheer for your allies to win the fight against behemoth bosses, you were rewarded for learning boss attack patterns, dodging perfectly, using your I-frames correctly, ressing when you were supposed to or straight up soloing the boss for some time until your friend could revive the others. I'm not sure if I want to recommend anyone to play Vindi anymore, it's sad at which state the game is, it's sad what's left of the community, how the game got dumbed down over the years, how much of payment stuff has been pushed into the game and how it essentially got ruined by Nexon, what used to be a relaxing action rpg that rewarded skill and allowed players to feel like they've beaten huge raid bosses or even dungeon bosses with friends and friendly allies, is now just a damaged shell of it's former glory. I have couple of thousands of hours in the game and honestly don't want to play it anymore. I'd rather keep some nice memories of Vindictus, rather than see the ruins that Nexon has managed to create out of it, through their complete greed and lack of care or understanding for the playerbase. And if anyone reads this wall of text, I'd advise you to avoid the game as well. Let it die please and don't support Nexon, let's hope that IF one day, there will be Vindictus 2, it will not be managed by them ever again. Warning : Avoid spending money in Nexon games, they have in not so long ago, leaked account passwords and also managed to let hackers get a hold of players credit cards and payment details, which were later used for large payments...Also, their in-game purchases suck at RNG, all is constructed in such a way that you will get drained of money and not receive items that you've wanted, all is in loot boxes. If you thought that EA is bad, you've never really played a game that Nexon was managing.", "appid": "212160", "steamid": "profiles/76561197995725101", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "114", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1564574400.0}
{"text": "Den Steam Controller kann man eigentlich nur unter einer Voraussetzung empfehlen und zwar wenn man damit langsame ruhige Strategie Games zocken will. Eventuell gehen Jump N Runs auch noch OK. Aber andere Sachen damit zu spielen ist eher eine Qual.  Wenn man Spiele zocken will die eh auf ein Gamepad ausgelegt sind sollte man lieber zu einem \"klassischem\" greifen. In 3rd Person und Ego Games vermisst man hier eindeutig den 2. Stick. Das umher schauen mit dem Trackpad ist eine Katastrophe. Klar wenn man sich dran gewöhnen möchte und sich laaange einarbeiten möchte funktioniert das bestimmt auch mit dieser Art Spielen. Muss man halt wissen ob man sich das antun möchte ;) Ich habe mir den Controller in erste Linie bestellt weil ich ihn sehr interessant fand (und auch immer noch finde) aber begeistern konnte er mich nicht.  Hier noch ein kurzes Pro & Contra: Pro: +Schicke Verarbeitung +Trackpads funktionieren als Maus sehr Gut +Sehr Große vielfalt an Einstellungsmöglichkeiten bzw die Möglichkeit CommunitySetups runterladen zu können +Die 2 Buttons auf der Rückseite, die finde ich echt gut und würde ich auch gern am X360 Pad haben  Contra: -Trackpads eignen sich nicht als Ersatz für einen Analog Stick -Braucht eine sehr lange Eingewöhnungsphase -ABYX Buttons zu klein -Insgesamt etwas zu klobig, liegt nicht so gut in der Hand wie ein 360 Pad -D-Pad als solches nicht gut gelungen. Zu groß und zu laut. -Keine Rumble Funktion Neutral: -Kein Akku sonder Normale Batterien (Stört mich eigentlich eher weniger) PS: Ich hab hier in den Reviews noch ein Youtube Video gefunden welches meine Meinung relativ gut wieder gibt ->", "appid": "353370", "steamid": "profiles/76561198019324303", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1447329600.0}
