{"text": "I am judging this game on a very low playtime, but the start to this was absolutely horrible. If I get a better PC, and have a chance to play co-op, I might reconsider this review, but for now, I'd say to hard pass on this game.  There is no feeling of actual role-play, or immersion of talking to NPCs out in the wild. Towns=safe, wilderness=unsafe. The combat feels like a scuffed Dark Souls, missing what actually made Dark Souls combat fun. The games main focus seems to be on combat, loot, and that's about it. I don't really see where the enjoyment is to be found, but after dying and losing everything with no way to get my stuff back, I just quit outright. It would be easier restarting than continuing that adventure, which the game seems to want you to do.  I just don't get it. It seems similar to Kenshi's hardcore RPG approach, but Kenshi has well written dialogue and a world that feels worth exploring. The systems are more in depth, and there is a save system. This game is lacking all of these features.", "appid": "794260", "steamid": "profiles/76561198069166359", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1600862400.0}
