{"text": "Hunt: Showdown is an absolutely brilliant competitive FPS with awe-inspiring visuals, cutting-edge graphics, addictive gameplay and excellent sound engineering that takes your situational awareness and cranks it up to eleven! Audio is the king in this game, and the 3D positional sound engine is the second best I have ever heard. To enjoy the full experience and even have a fighting chance, a decent pair of headphones is a must have. The game puts up to 10 players which can consist of solo lone wolves or duo groups in a massive map, with the objective being to hunt down a formidable boss monster and escape with its bounty before other players (or monsters) kill you. In order to track down the boss, there are clues lying around in random places that can be interacted with to get you closer to your target. There are also extraction points around the map which can be used at any time to escape. While that may not sound innovative or really impressive at first, there's a major twist: You have absolutely no way of knowing how many other players there are on the map (unless they are carrying the bounty)! There is no scoreboard or kill feed. You have to manually keep track of every player death yourself and even then you can never know whether some have extracted early or if the server even started with 10 players in the first place. This results in extreme tension and paranoia; you will truly fear the environment itself since a hostile hunter could be lurking anywhere. Your hunter can easily become the hunted. There is an expansive list of weapons, items and equipment to choose from and they each serve a purpose. Hunter loadouts can be quite varied making each match a fresh experience. Although some weapons could use a bit of work in terms of balancing, the game is still in Early Access so there's still a lot of room for improvement in the future. The developers have done a great job of listening to community feedback so far. Last but not least, that brings us to the game's technical performance and optimization,   it's been improved tremendously since the initial launch and runs rather decently now on a wide range of hardware specs. - Intuitive user interface - Great attention to detail - Addictive and fun core Gameplay - Remarkable aesthetic and art style - Rock solid netcode; hitreg is spot on - Supports Borderless Windowed mode - Innovative concept and amazing execution - Surprisingly simple and easy control scheme - A huge arsenal of weapons, tools and equipment - Breathtaking scenery; the graphics are mind-blowing - Deep and engaging atmosphere; tension is always high - Decent progression system and character customization - Excellent sound design; one of the best in recent history - Satisfying shooting and well-designed Stealth mechanics - Scarce resources and limited ammunition - Steep learning curve and difficult to master - Camping is prevalent and a very effective strategy - Heavy focus on duo groups; solo play is discouraged - Almost pitch black nights; very close to absolute darkness - In-game voice/text chat can be heard/seen by enemies in proximity - Death is permanent; dead hunters and all their equipment will be lost - Bullets are projectiles, meaning they have travel distance and that takes time - Slow and methodical; requires tactical approach and excellent decision making - Apart from Bounty Carrier(s), there is no way to know if there are other Players in the match -  ✝ - Generic and uninspired monster design - Lackluster soundtrack (music variety) and practically no voice acting -  ✝ - Imperfect game balance; hunters and equipment could use some fine-tuning overall✝ - Underwhelming PVE aspects; monsters and bosses are quite weak and easy to defeat - Poor in-game presentation of lore; story is somewhat nonexistent and mostly unexplored -  ✝ ✝   9.25/10 - Masterpiece Hunt: Showdown is a true masterpiece and one of the greatest games I have played in recent memory. It brings a novel twist to a tried and true concept and executes it perfectly. The competitive nature of it and the infinite skill-ceiling makes it a great long term investment and a game that you will sink hundreds or thousands of hours into. If you have any passion for first-person shooter games, you must give this game a try. I strongly recommend Hunt:Showdown to any fan of video games, it's a brilliant games that can provide countless hours of memorable experience.", "appid": "594650", "steamid": "profiles/76561197963259080", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1531137600.0}
