{"text": "1 hour in, here's my review: -Graphics: 3/10, Seriously, I've seen better graphics on a video tutorial of Windows XP. (imagine the circus-ugly child of Team Fortress 2 and Firefall, except worse.) -Sound: 6/10, Creepy enough to set a mood, but nothing groundbreaking.  -Mechanics: 5/10, controls were easy enough to understand, pretty good crafting system. The map leaves much to be desired though. -Performace: 0.5/10, oh god. Where do I begin. You'd imagine with a gaming computer with a price tag in the quadruple digits I'd get a pretty steady framerate, right? Wrong. 25 FPS is the highest I saw even on minimum graphics with everything else turned off. I get better frame rates running Warface at Max graphics. In the time it took for the game to register the \"forward\" command, I could have actually gone back to school and done something useful with my life. (dont get me started on the lag spikes) -Realism: 7/10, You can lose all your items on death, you have very limited backpack space, you dont start out with an AWP and enough money to buy Donald Trump, and not every house you raid has wall to wall cashes of Food and ammunition. (all good), but to put that in perspective, you can walk through most zombies...  -Stability: 4/10, Just enough bugs to make your skin crawl. only 1 crash so far.  I'm curious where the devs take this, I'll try to update this review as I play more.", "appid": "349700", "steamid": "profiles/76561198176297517", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1450094400.0}
