{"text": "This game was so dissappointing that I am actually angry. Do not get fooled by the nice artstyle and the interesting topic. The screesnshots on the store page already show everything there is to this game. The gameplay loop consists of reading e-mails with information everyone who has even slightly researched this topic already knows, followed by the \"interactive\" sequences of preparing a body, during which the game tells you where exactly to click step-by-step every single time you do it. Afterwards you get to click an arrow on the ground to go to the other room, where you can click on the coffin or urn and click on the relatives to make a speech bubble with a pointless remark (\"She would have loved this funeral!\") appear, click another arrow to go back to your e-mails. Rinse and repeat for about 45 -60 minutes, depending on how you fast you can work through the mails. This should be free. Avoid at all cost.", "appid": "578720", "steamid": "profiles/76561198128285066", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "6", "votes_funny": "1", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1604404800.0}
{"text": "Игра хорошая. Я не спорю. Озвучка, графика, геймплей... Все на высоте! Но все испортило то, что не хотел опознавать мой руль. По этому я не смог насладиться игрой.  П.С. : я заходил в настройки, там даже не смог ничего сделать", "appid": "223670", "steamid": "profiles/76561198104711875", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": 0, "votes_funny": 0, "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1395057600.0}
{"text": "First off, the game is actually pretty fun. Though I mostly played on the non-steam version and have a lot more hours than just what is shown. In any case. As someone who doesn't like PvP at all, in BDO its probably the most \"carebear\" PvP I've ever seen in a PvP MMO. So much so that as a PVEr it doesn't bother me at all. For one, dying in pvp gives you no penalties at all. If you die in PVE you lose EXP, so dying in PVE is actually vastly worse. And the game has a TON of PVE content, housing, crafting, worker empire building and all kinds of stuff. The housing system is actually really great and one of the better ones. Its definitely more than just grinding mobs 24/7. The problem is the community that plays this game. Political bot spam (and sure political trolls and bots in all MMOs even WoW, but in BDO its a ton worse), trolls in general, people that pretend to be pedophiles (or maybe they aren't pretending which is scary) and the community is just generally one of the worst. Its definitely not the worst community I've seen in an MMO, but its definitely up there.  And when one plays an MMO, its generally for the community and other people that play it, and who wants to play an MMO with such a terrible community unless they are also terrible?", "appid": "582660", "steamid": "profiles/76561198007338817", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "49", "votes_funny": "4", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1599393600.0}
