{"text": "There is no conditional recommendation feature on Steam, because of this I cannot recommend, however the program can be useful to would be flight simmers. The idea behind Dovetail Games Flight School is to give newcomers to the genre a taste of what flight sims are all about at a reasonable price. For me it misses the mark, though the price is reasonable. The program offers the ability to gain two pilots licences by completing various tasks that form part of the basic mechanics of general aviation flying. It doesn’t give much by way of an understanding though, it is good at telling you what to do, but not as good at telling you why. The program also offers a number of missions of varying difficulty. These are fun, but are at the same time quite frustrating. Finally the program also offers the ability to freely fly anywhere on the planet using the two (soon to be three) supplied aircraft. I have used the program for just over 9 hours at the time of writing and my overall experience can only be described as one of frustration. I have over a thousand hours under my belt with FSX:SE and FSX before it, I found the amount of information made available to the pilot prior to any task or mission lacking. Simple things, like what the heading is of the runway you are being sent to for a mission, some of the strips are very tight. If you aren’t able to set up a good approach it just makes things more difficult and frustrating.  In the lessons, you don’t get to find out exactly what you are going to do until you are trying to trim the aircraft, monitor the speed/throttle and check your heading while the instructor is also filling you in on the facts as to why you are in the air in the first place. This usually results in a failure of that particular mission/task, lots of swearing at the monitor and another attempt. At least you have a better understanding of what the objective is second or third time round. Now I haven’t been to flight school IRL, I do think though that I would receive a full briefing of what todays lesson was going to be before I got anywhere near the aircraft. If you can ride the waves of frustration and persevere with the lessons/missions, there is a sense of achievement upon completion. If you do this, there is a good chance that you will enjoy a step up to FSX, P3D, X-Plane or DTG’s upcoming Flight Simulator, so maybe the program is really just one big test. Despite community hub complaints, I find the graphics far better than many of the available flight sims that have global coverage out of the box. Just make sure your rig comfortably meets the spec requirements and you will have access to a program that performs and looks as good as a £100+ spend on other sims for the sweet price of £11, though there is room for some improvement (clouds, sky, mid-day ambient lighting). To summarise. It’s a cheap way to find out if you are willing to shell out substantially more on a good flight simulator. If you can put up with the programs foibles it is a good indication that this genre is for you. <TL;DR> If you are just testing the water for flight simming this will put you off more than encourage you to progress. If you think it is something you really want to get into, a little perseverance will help in making your mind up. </TL;DR>", "appid": "441920", "steamid": "profiles/76561198030867254", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "82", "votes_funny": "5", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1464436800.0}
{"text": "I have been playing this game for over 3 years and a i can assure you there is nothing more stressing to experience everytime you play!  I have reached red ranks as killer and i have a lot of experience in the game so i know what im talking about! The map design of this game is terrrible bad designed, where the 4 survivors are always in constant advantage in any point of the game, as a killer you depend on them to do mistakes so you can actually win! There is only one exception but you would be forced to play \"the nurse\" everytime you want to play killer letting the other 21 one killers completly useless, the maps are extremly big making so that a killer is in constant stress and forces him to be everywhere anywhere which is quite literally impossible! There are around 15 pallets in which map that are MOSTLY safe, not to count infinite loops and window vaults, the meta has no variaty, as the survivors can win the game with builds full of second chances perks, making the killer pressure nule! If the survivors are coordenated and skillfull they can win the game in under 4 minutes, and the killer HAS NO WAY TO PREVENT THIS except if you are using the nurse! I would not recommend you to touch on this game if you are planning to try out to play killer! It will stress you and make you mad every time you try to play and climb! The part of the community that only plays survivors is extremly toxic and will make sure to make fun of you and make your experience even worse!  This game should have a look at their map design and remove unfun mecanics from both survivor and killer side, implement more teamwork and wipeout a little of the community, 80% of the maps are survivor favored they should rework second chance perks, remove Bloodlust from killers and buff each singular individual to have a fighting chance and make all of them a little more competitive to use compared to the top tiers. In a game where the killer is supposed to be the strong unit and make the game challanging to the other team is ALWAYS THE UNDERDOG the game is never in their favor if survivors do mistakes, even in the emblem system where you are scored from how many hooks you make and not how many kills/sacrifices, the \"Gatekeeper\" emblem makes no sense since killers have very low/none chances to slow them down if the survivors are split up, since it's release the game has been in a unhealthy state, from a community aspect to a game balance aspect and i would not recomend to buy it if you want to have fun playing games", "appid": "381210", "steamid": "profiles/76561198136240521", "voted_up": false, "votes_up": "1", "votes_funny": "6", "early_access": false, "tstamp_created": 1593777600.0}
